GF Chocolate Chip Cookies

- 250g white beans, rinsed and with water squeezed out (weigh after squeezing water out - so it might be 1 x 400g can + a bit)
- 1/2 c tahini (well-stirred, not too runny)
- 1/4 c maple syrup
- 1 tsp vanilla extract
- 1 tbsp lemon juice
- 1 tsp baking powder
- 1/8 tsp salt
- 3/4 c vegan dark chocolate chips or chopped chocolate

Puree everything except chocolate chips, then fold in the chips. Divvy up on a cookie sheet and bake until done.

Notes: Since no instructions were provided for the recipe, it's just an educated guess. Probably bake at 350F for 8-10 min ymmv. Makes 10
